net.varkhan.base.containers.queue
Class OpenHeapQueue<Type>

java.lang.Object
  net.varkhan.base.containers.queue.OpenHeapQueue<Type>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable, Container<Type>, Queue<Type>, Visitable<Type>
public class OpenHeapQueue<Type>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Queue<Type>

A generic heap-based unbounded priority queue.

This class uses an extensible heap to provide the semantics of a priority queue on objects, either naturally ordered as per the Comparable interface, or ordered by a Comparator.

When the number of elements equals the current size of the heap, the heap is extended. It does not shrink when elements are removed, but can be made to fit the number of elements in the queue by calling the pack() method.
